Quick Summary

  Allowed:
  - Calling xlibs functions from your mod (intended use)
  - Use in modpacks (encouraged)
  - Addons, patches, integrations that depend on xlibs
  - Personal use and configuration
  - Reading source and docs to use, extend, or debug the software
  - Using AI tools to learn how to use the public API
  - Independent implementations that do not reproduce this
    software's implementation

  Required:
  - Visible credit: xlibs by Damian Sirbu

  Not allowed:
  - Reproducing the software's implementation to build
    standalone replacements (even with credit)
  - Reverse engineering internals to reproduce implementation
  - Using automated tools to extract implementation for
    reproduction in other software

  Full terms below.

